article.headline: S. Dakota St. 93, Dakota State 60
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. -- Chad White scored 22 points Monday night as South Dakota State ran its winning streak to five with a 93-60 victory over Dakota State. Taevaunn Prince added 15 points for the Jackrabbits (9-3), while Jordan Dykstra had 12, Griffan Callahan 11 and Zach Horstman 10. Brayden Carlson had eight assists and five steals. Luke Lamb scored 16 points to lead the Trojans. Cameron Krump had 11 and Jesse Bean 10. The Trojans were outshot 53-42 percent, were outrebounded 45-24 and were outscored 40-20 in the paint. The Jackrabbits led only 31-26 with 6:04 to go in the first half, but a 17-4 run to close the half made it 48-30 at the break, and the lead ranged as high as 38 late in the game. NAIA Division II Dakota State (7-4) had been idle since Dec. 3 and played the game as an exhibition.
